                <h2>
                    About A.P.J Abdul Kalam</h2>
                    <p>A.P.J. Abdul Kalam, the "Missile Man of India," was born on October 15, 1931, in Rameswaram, Tamil Nadu. He served as the 11th President of India and was a renowned scientist, known for his work in India's space and missile programs.</p> </p>
                    </p>

            </section>
<section class ="achievements">
<h2>Achievements</h2>
<ul>
<li>Developed India's first satellite launch vehicle(SLV-III)
</li>
<li>Led India's first successful nuclear tests in 1998 
</li>

<li>Wrote books like "Wings of Fire" and "India 2020"</li>
<li>Received Bharat Ratna, India's highest civilian award</li>

</ul>
</section>

